[The main new bit of info here is that his wife and child are confined too,
and that over 100 people are being examined - LC
[The patient was brought for safety confinement to the Virchow Clinic in
Berlin with his wife and child because he was bleeding through his eyes and
ears.
The British Broadcasting Corp. reports today that [the patient´s biologist
companion has not yet shown any signs of illness, and that health officials
are now saying it is unlikely that whatever afflicts [him passed on to
anyone else. [But the BBC also reports more than 100 people who've come
into contact with the 2 men are undergoing thorough check-ups.
A tropical disease alert has arisen in Germany before. In 1967 seven people
died following an outbreak of the Marburg virus in Frankfurt.
--
[That one was in vaccine plant workers handling monkeys imported from
Uganda - Mod.JW
